&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/cybernetic-postliberalism/texts/the-ecclesial-recurrence/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/cybernetic-postliberalism/texts/the-ecclesial-recurrence/> ;
  schema:name "The Ecclesial Recurrence" ;
  schema:description "Californication is recurrent across the modern pastoral apparatus; the medieval Christian church is its most thoroughly developed prior institutional form. What is recurrent: continuous calibration of inner life through pastoral relations and specific affective genres (acedia, spes, studiositas, curiositas). What is changed: the energetic substrate is inverted, latency has collapsed, protected interiors are gone, the contradictions metabolized differ." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-04-27" ;
